This module contains seq-based containers useful in contexts that make use of data-oriented design

Types

OrdinalSeq[I; T] = distinct seq[T]
Similar to a seq, but can only be accessed by values of the specified type. This is useful in situations where the type of the index value is a distinct integer-like type   Source   Edit 
SeqMap[K; V] = object
  data: seq[V]
Maps a 0-based integer-like key to a value, using a seq as the underlying storage. The default value for V is expected to indicated "empty" and an isFilled routine that returns a bool must exist for V   Source   Edit 
Store[I; T] = object
  data: seq[T]
Stores a sequence of T where each item is identified by an integer-like ID. The container is append-only   Source   Edit
